{{see|Taste}}
==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}  {{countable}} ''and'' {{uncountable}}

# One of the sensations produced by the [[tongue]] in response to certain chemicals often confused and/or mixed somewhat with [[smell]]ing. The primary sensations classified as taste are: [[sweet]], [[sour]], [[bitter]], [[salty]] and [[umami]].
# {{countable}} and {{uncountable}}: A person’s generic, implicit set of preferences, especially esthetic, though also culinary, sartorial, etc.
#: ''Dr. Parker has good '''taste''' in wine.''  

